## {{ drug.molecular_formula }}

Magnesium Stearate contains not less than 3.8 per cent and not more than 5.0 per cent of Mg, calculated with reference to the dried substance.

Identification: A: To 5.{{ drug.strength }} add {{ drug.strength }} of ether, {{ drug.strength }} of 2M nitric acid and {{ drug.strength }} of distilled water and heat under a reflux condenser until dissolution is complete. Allow to cool, separate the aqueous layer and shake the ether layer with two quantities, each of {{ drug.strength }}, of distilled water. Combine the aqueous layers, wash with {{ drug.strength }} of ether and dilute to {{ drug.strength }} with distilled water ({{ drug.dosage_form }} A). Evaporate the ether layer to dryness and dry the residue at 105o. The freezing point of the residue is not lower than 53o.

B: {{ drug.strength }} of {{ drug.dosage_form }} A obtained in test A gives reaction A of magnesium salts.

Acidity or alkalinity: Mix {{ drug.strength }} with {{ drug.strength }} of carbon dioxide-free water, boil for 1 minute, shaking continuously, cool and filter. To {{ drug.strength }} of filtrate add 0.{{ drug.strength }} of bromothymol blue {{ drug.dosage_form }}. Not more than 0.{{ drug.strength }} of 0.1M hydrochloric acid or 0.1M sodium hydroxide is required to change the colour of the {{ drug.dosage_form }}.

Colour of {{ drug.dosage_form }}: {{ drug.dosage_form }} A is not more intensely coloured than reference {{ drug.dosage_form }} YS6.

Clarity and colour of {{ drug.dosage_form }} of the fatty acids: Dissolve 0.{{ drug.strength }} of the residue obtained in the preparation of {{ drug.dosage_form }} A in {{ drug.strength }} of chloroform. The {{ drug.dosage_form }} is clear, and not more intensely coloured than reference {{ drug.dosage_form }} YS5.

Acid value of the fatty acids: Between 195 and 210, determined on 0.{{ drug.strength }} of the residue obtained in the preparation of {{ drug.dosage_form }} A dissolved in {{ drug.strength }} of the prescribed mixture of solvents.

Free stearic acid: Not more than 3%, determined by the following method. Weigh accurately about {{ drug.strength }} into a stoppered flask, add {{ drug.strength }} of chloroform, stopper the flask and shake well. Filter into a beaker through two thicknesses of filter paper taking care to avoid evaporation of the solvent. Wash the filter with {{ drug.strength }} of chloroform and collect the washings in the beaker. Evaporate the chloroform on a water-bath in a current of air. Dissolve the residue in about {{ drug.strength }} of ethanol (95%) previously neutralised to phenolphthalein {{ drug.dosage_form }} and titrate with 0.1M sodium hydroxide using phenolphthalein {{ drug.dosage_form }} as indicator. Each ml of 0.1M sodium hydroxide is equivalent to 0.{{ drug.strength }} of stearic acid.

Zinc stearate: Heat {{ drug.strength }} with shaking with a mixture of {{ drug.strength }} of water and {{ drug.strength }} of dilute sulphuric acid until the fatty acids separate as an oily layer. Cool, filter the aqueous layer and wash the residue with two successive quantities, each of {{ drug.strength }}, of hot water, combine the filtrate and the washings and dilute to {{ drug.strength }} with water. To {{ drug.strength }} of the resulting {{ drug.dosage_form }} add 0.{{ drug.strength }} of ammonium mercurithiocyanate {{ drug.dosage_form }} and 0.{{ drug.strength }} of copper sulphate {{ drug.dosage_form }}. Scratch the walls of the container with a glass rod and allow to stand for 15 minutes; no violet precipitate is formed.

Heavy metals: Not more than 20 ppm, determined by Method D on {{ drug.strength }} of a {{ drug.dosage_form }} prepared in the following manner. Heat 5.{{ drug.strength }} with {{ drug.strength }} of 2M acetic acid and allow to cool. Filter, wash the residue with two quantities, each of {{ drug.strength }}, of warm water and dilute to {{ drug.strength }} with water. Use 1.{{ drug.strength }} of lead standard {{ drug.dosage_form }} (10 ppm Pb) to prepare the standard {{ drug.dosage_form }}.

Chloride: {{ drug.strength }} of {{ drug.dosage_form }} A diluted to {{ drug.strength }} complies with the limit test for chlorides.(250 ppm).

Sulphate: Dilute 5.{{ drug.strength }} of {{ drug.dosage_form }} A to 50.{{ drug.strength }} with water. 2.{{ drug.strength }} of this {{ drug.dosage_form }} diluted to {{ drug.strength }} with water complies with the limit test for sulphate. (0.6%) (amendment 1).

Loss on drying: Not more than 6.0%, determined on {{ drug.strength }} by drying in an oven at 105o.

Assay: Weigh accurately about 0.{{ drug.strength }}, add {{ drug.strength }} of a mixture of equal volumes of (amendment 1)1-butanol and ethanol, {{ drug.strength }} of strong ammonia {{ drug.dosage_form }}, {{ drug.strength }} of ammonia buffer pH 10.0, 30.{{ drug.strength }} of 0.1M disodium edetate and {{ drug.strength }} of mordant black 11 mixtures, heat to 45o to 50o and titrate with 0.1M zinc sulphate until the colour changes from blue to violet. Repeat the operation without the substance being examined. The difference between the titrations represents the amount of disodium edetate required. Each ml of 0.1M disodium edetate is equivalent to 0.{{ drug.strength }} of Mg.
